{
  "texts": [
    "The literature rarely discusses the prediction of turnover as unbalanced classes to the best of our knowledge.",
    "The number of positive cases is much smaller than negative, although we support machine learning with the synthetic minority oversampling technique (SMOTE) 20, a balancing technique that significantly increases the accuracy of the prediction 21. 5.",
    "Throughout the process, we strive to maintain explainability because, in addition to the accuracy of the prediction, it is also important for managers and decision-makers to have explanations. 6.",
    "We combine the prediction of employee turnover with an explainable machine learning method and use the Shapley Additive exPlanation (SHAP) 22 technique to measure the marginal contribution of variables to each individual prediction.",
    "Common anomaly patterns are uncovered in clusters based on SHAP values to handle the complexity of finding individuals with similarly important predictors."
  ]
}